82
00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:12.437
And this evaluates to zero if the covariance between x and y is zero,

83
00:06:12.437 --> 00:06:16.620
and that is the case when x and y are uncorrelated.

84
00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:20.206
Coming back now to our geometric interpretation,

85
00:06:20.206 --> 00:06:30.655
we would now replace a with the standard deviation of x,

86
00:06:30.655 --> 00:06:36.050
b is the standard deviation of y,

87
00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:42.000
and c is the square root of

88
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:50.884
the variance of x plus the variance of y.

89
00:06:50.884 --> 00:06:56.050
And this is how we get our geometric interpretation of random variables.

90
